00:46.747 --> 00:48.216
* Stop gettin' mad at me

00:48.249 --> 00:49.783
* Sunday to Saturday
[ Both giggle ]

00:49.817 --> 00:51.219
* We fightin' gravity

00:51.252 --> 00:53.254
* And if you stuck
on the ground *

00:53.287 --> 00:54.722
* Stop gettin' mad at me

00:54.755 --> 00:56.090
* Get lifted
[ Laughing ] Aah! Ha!

00:56.124 --> 00:57.525
* Get light
Ha! Ha!

00:57.558 --> 01:00.228
* Throw your hands up
in the sky *

01:00.261 --> 01:02.363
* But we can still get lifted

01:02.396 --> 01:04.064
* Get light

01:04.098 --> 01:05.999
[ Gulls crying ]

01:07.135 --> 01:09.970
Hm, I wish
these weren't so salty.

01:10.003 --> 01:11.805
Steve! Steve-Steve!

01:11.839 --> 01:12.973
Steeeve!

01:13.006 --> 01:14.908
You. Me.
Water-rocket boots.

01:14.942 --> 01:17.478
Everyone else --
eyes like these.

01:17.511 --> 01:18.946
[ Ting! ]

01:18.979 --> 01:21.149
You know I don't go
in the ocean.

01:21.182 --> 01:22.883
I've got
a shark phobia.

01:22.916 --> 01:25.052
You're afraid of sharks?
That ridiculous.

01:25.085 --> 01:27.087
Just look at you.
You're too afraid
to be in the sun.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.589
You're too afraid
to go in the water.

01:28.622 --> 01:31.091
Oh, let me guess,
you're too afraid to eat sand?

01:31.125 --> 01:32.793
Not really afraid...

01:32.826 --> 01:34.562
Fear is
a mental prison.

01:34.595 --> 01:36.697
Behold,
the power of the mind!

01:38.532 --> 01:40.234
Jesus, Dad!

01:40.268 --> 01:43.404
[ Weakly ]
And this...is what...

01:43.437 --> 01:45.105
a free man looks like.

01:45.139 --> 01:46.140
[ Bucket thuds ]

01:46.174 --> 01:47.608
[ Thud ]
[ Groans ]

01:47.641 --> 01:49.577
Wow, you're not afraid
of anything.

01:49.610 --> 01:51.345
Are you afraid
of little kisses?

01:51.379 --> 01:52.846
Mwah!

01:52.880 --> 01:54.782
How about a little kiss
on your chin?

01:54.815 --> 01:56.016
Mwah!

01:56.049 --> 01:57.084
How 'bout your belly?

01:57.117 --> 01:58.452
Mwah!

01:58.486 --> 02:01.155
And what's this?
Oh, hello!

02:01.189 --> 02:02.823
Mwah!

02:02.856 --> 02:05.626
**

02:05.659 --> 02:07.995
* Good morning, U.S.A.

02:08.028 --> 02:11.832
* I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day *

02:11.865 --> 02:14.968
* The sun in the sky
has a smile on his face *

02:15.002 --> 02:19.373
* And he's shinin' a salute
to the American race *

02:21.209 --> 02:24.645
* Oh, boy, it's swell to say

02:24.678 --> 02:27.114
* Good --
* Good morning, U.S.A.

02:27.147 --> 02:28.182
Aah!

02:29.517 --> 02:32.820
* Good morning, U.S.A.

02:32.853 --> 02:35.323
**

02:35.356 --> 02:36.857
Sorry about that whole

02:36.890 --> 02:38.959
"going down on you at the beach"
misunderstanding.

02:38.992 --> 02:40.628
Here's a free
Bloody Mary.

02:40.661 --> 02:43.831
But with SpaghettiO sauce and
a Twizzler instead of celery.

02:43.864 --> 02:46.867
Alcoholic drinks for kids
are an untapped market.

02:46.900 --> 02:48.369
No one ever thinks
of the children.

02:48.402 --> 02:50.704
I can't stop thinking
about a child.

02:50.738 --> 02:52.039
My child.

02:52.072 --> 02:53.874
The Steve-child.

02:53.907 --> 02:57.177
Cool. So I guess we're done
with what I was talking about?

02:57.211 --> 02:59.513
Steve's shark phobia
is just the start.

02:59.547 --> 03:01.582
If he continues to be
a slave to his fears,

03:01.615 --> 03:03.217
he's gonna
miss out on life.

03:03.251 --> 03:06.086
Hey! Maybe Dr. Penguin could
help him work through it.

03:06.119 --> 03:08.589
Oh, Stan.
Dr. Penguin died.

03:08.622 --> 03:10.324
Did you not get invited
to the funeral?

03:10.358 --> 03:12.025
It was a tiny,
little thing...

03:12.059 --> 03:13.327
at the Spearmint Rhino.

03:13.361 --> 03:14.862
Super intimate.
Are you finished?

03:14.895 --> 03:16.430
There wasn't a dry thigh
in the --

03:16.464 --> 03:18.198
Roger!
What do I do about Steve?

03:18.232 --> 03:20.668
Well, as my mentor,
Dr. Penguin --

03:20.701 --> 03:22.503
RIP, one love,
gone but not forgotten --

03:22.536 --> 03:25.539
used to say, "When you're forced
to confront a fear,

03:25.573 --> 03:27.341
that fear loses
its power."

03:27.375 --> 03:29.243
Yeah!
That sounds like a thing!

03:29.277 --> 03:30.511
It sure is.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.912
And I happen to have
another persona

03:31.945 --> 03:33.614
that could help
with Steve's problem.

03:33.647 --> 03:35.616
Just get him in the ocean,
and I'll do the rest.
Great.

03:35.649 --> 03:38.919
Wow, so Penguin died, huh?
What happened?

03:38.952 --> 03:40.388
It came out of nowhere.

03:40.421 --> 03:42.423
He saw a movie he liked
at Sundance,

03:42.456 --> 03:44.925
just walked off
into the forest.

03:44.958 --> 03:46.294
Danuta, I can't wait

03:46.327 --> 03:47.695
to hear all about
your semester in Chile.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.597
Girl, I bet you
learned to fry up

03:49.630 --> 03:51.632
a badass
bloomin' onion.

03:51.665 --> 03:53.634
Not Chili's, Mom.
Chile.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.202
It's a country.

03:55.235 --> 03:58.105
Ah, you girls
keep me young.
[ Door opens ]

03:58.138 --> 04:00.541
So, my Saturn's officially
a piece of shit.

04:00.574 --> 04:02.276
I had to take it
to the shop again,

04:02.310 --> 04:04.445
so I'll be catching the bus
for the next week.

04:04.478 --> 04:06.880
The one positive is that
riding with all those low-lifes

04:06.914 --> 04:08.549
is a real
confidence booster.

04:08.582 --> 04:10.484
I feel like freakin' JFK
on there.

04:10.518 --> 04:13.587
Guess that makes the homeless
guy whacking off in the aisle

04:13.621 --> 04:15.323
my Jackie O.

04:15.356 --> 04:16.824
What's his deal?

04:16.857 --> 04:19.159
He's...kinda hot.

04:19.192 --> 04:20.494
Klaus?
[ Retches ]

04:20.528 --> 04:22.262
Yeah, he seems funny.

04:22.296 --> 04:24.965
I mean,
if he's even available.

04:24.998 --> 04:28.068
Uh, he goes to the DMV
"just to chill."

04:28.101 --> 04:29.303
I think he's available.

04:29.337 --> 04:30.404
Hook it up, then.

04:30.438 --> 04:31.939
Enough about Klaus.

04:31.972 --> 04:34.074
Our girl's
back in town.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.310
So, what else have
you been up to, Danuta?

04:36.344 --> 04:37.745
Start at birth

04:37.778 --> 04:40.648
since this is the first time
we've ever met.

04:40.681 --> 04:43.984
How ya likin'
old Francine so far?

04:46.820 --> 04:50.123
**

04:50.157 --> 04:51.625
Ahh.

04:51.659 --> 04:53.160
[ Bang, clatter ]

04:53.193 --> 04:56.697
[ Wood creaking ]

04:57.898 --> 04:59.132
[ Thud ]

04:59.166 --> 05:00.601
[ Clang ]

05:00.634 --> 05:02.169
Oh, my God!

05:02.202 --> 05:03.671
Ahoy there!
[ Sizzle ]

05:03.704 --> 05:05.105
Can I dog ya,
my man?

05:05.138 --> 05:06.540
Where am I?!

05:06.574 --> 05:08.141
Uh, the ocean?

05:08.175 --> 05:10.378
A percentage of the world
is covered in it.

05:10.411 --> 05:11.512
Just ribbin' ya, son.

05:11.545 --> 05:12.780
I know you're confused

05:12.813 --> 05:14.281
because of
my unnecessary trick.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.016
Did you feel
like a giant in there?

05:16.049 --> 05:18.318
The whole room
was 7/8th scale.

05:18.352 --> 05:20.053
That was the second part
of my trick.

05:20.087 --> 05:21.622
Here's the third part.
Aaaaaah!

05:21.655 --> 05:22.856
[ Splash ]

05:22.890 --> 05:24.658
Aaaaaah!

05:24.692 --> 05:26.193
Don't trick me back,
Steve.

05:26.226 --> 05:28.295
I can dish it out,
but I cannot take it.

05:28.328 --> 05:30.864
Aah! Aah! Aah!

05:30.898 --> 05:32.533
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

05:32.566 --> 05:35.002
Aaaah!

05:35.035 --> 05:38.639
Shark-shark-shark-shark-shark-
shark-shark-shark-shark!

05:38.672 --> 05:40.474
[ Screaming ]
Come on, ya little wuss.

05:40.508 --> 05:42.075
Hit me so I can
get out of here.

05:42.109 --> 05:43.544
[ Whimpering ]

05:43.577 --> 05:45.479
[ Smack ]
[ Yelps ]

05:45.513 --> 05:48.449
[ Yelping ]

05:50.250 --> 05:52.686
Oh, my God, Steve!
[ Panting ]

05:52.720 --> 05:54.855
You were just face-to-face
with a shark.

05:54.888 --> 05:56.824
I -- I was terrified.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.659
But I was
splashing around

05:58.692 --> 06:00.828
and -- and bopped him
on the nose,

06:00.861 --> 06:02.930
and I think
I scared him.

06:02.963 --> 06:05.699
I'd say he was probably
more afraid than you were.

06:05.733 --> 06:07.768
I kicked his ass.

06:07.801 --> 06:10.938
I just kicked
that shark's ass!

06:10.971 --> 06:12.940
I made that shark
my bitch!

06:12.973 --> 06:16.276
Looks like tuna isn't
the only chicken of the sea.

06:16.309 --> 06:18.512
See?
Nothing to worry about.
You're right.

06:18.546 --> 06:20.881
'Cause I dominated
a friggin' shark.

06:20.914 --> 06:22.215
Up top!

06:22.249 --> 06:23.451
[ Dramatic music plays ]

06:23.484 --> 06:24.718
[ Bone crunches ]

06:24.752 --> 06:26.954
Aaaaaaaaah!

06:26.987 --> 06:28.221
[ Both scream ]

06:28.255 --> 06:30.891
[ Blood trickles ]

06:30.924 --> 06:32.059
[ Splat ]

06:32.092 --> 06:33.861
Thank God,
the bleeding stopped.

06:33.894 --> 06:36.096
I think
I'm out of bloo...

06:36.129 --> 06:39.266
You're gonna be okay, son.
Stay with me.

06:39.299 --> 06:42.470
There.
There's my angel's smile.

06:45.338 --> 06:47.641
**

06:47.675 --> 06:50.744
Holy hell, Roger.
How could you bite
Steve's arm off?

06:50.778 --> 06:52.780
Now he's gonna be afraid
of his own shadow.

06:52.813 --> 06:55.082
What you're forgetting
is the very important lesson

06:55.115 --> 06:56.484
I did teach him --

06:56.517 --> 06:58.285
don't talk shit
about sharks.

06:58.318 --> 07:01.388
Just give me back his arm
so the doctor can reattach it.

07:01.421 --> 07:04.825
[ Gagging ]

07:04.858 --> 07:05.926
[ Splat ]

07:05.959 --> 07:07.327
Should be
good as new --

07:07.360 --> 07:09.162
My stomach runs about
10° Fahrenheit.

07:09.196 --> 07:10.430
It comes in very handy.

07:10.464 --> 07:11.799
Did you know
I'm the number-three

07:11.832 --> 07:13.967
Carvel franchise in the state
of Virginia?

07:14.001 --> 07:15.503
Want me to puke you up
a sundae

07:15.536 --> 07:17.471
in one of those cute little
baseball helmets?

07:17.505 --> 07:18.639
Who's your team, Stan?

07:18.672 --> 07:20.073
Hope you're
a Marlins fans!

07:20.107 --> 07:25.112
[ Gagging ]

07:26.480 --> 07:27.915
Steve?

07:27.948 --> 07:29.282
I brought you
a little something

07:29.316 --> 07:31.184
to say sorry about
what happened.

07:31.218 --> 07:32.953
I'm not sorry
it happened.

07:32.986 --> 07:34.421
Wha-- What?

07:34.454 --> 07:36.690
I came face-to-face
with my greatest fear,

07:36.724 --> 07:38.626
and I made it out
the other side.

07:38.659 --> 07:39.993
You were right.

07:40.027 --> 07:42.029
I've wasted my whole life
living in fear.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.997
Well, I'm finally free.

07:44.031 --> 07:46.433
No more closing my eyes
in the cereal aisle

07:46.466 --> 07:48.168
for fear
of seeing Boo Berry.

07:48.201 --> 07:50.838
And I'm gonna wear this stump
as a badge of honor --

07:50.871 --> 07:53.874
a reminder to not be afraid
of anything.

07:53.907 --> 07:56.443
No even the dread pirate,
Captain Crunch.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.879
Wow.
Really?

07:58.912 --> 08:00.480
I thought
you'd be...

08:00.514 --> 08:01.615
Now, what'd you
bring me?

08:01.649 --> 08:03.350
Uh...

08:04.552 --> 08:08.455
Hey!
I brought you
this Dikembe Mutombo jersey.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.957
Can I help ya,
buddy?

08:09.990 --> 08:12.192
I'm just trying to talk
to my deformed son,

08:12.225 --> 08:13.561
and you're just
standing there,

08:13.594 --> 08:15.328
binge-watching
the whole conversation.

08:15.362 --> 08:16.964
Put the jersey on,
Steve.

08:16.997 --> 08:20.033
That jersey looks real good
on ya, Steve.

08:20.067 --> 08:21.669
Buying that jersey
for you

08:21.702 --> 08:24.404
was one of the great joys
of my life.

08:24.437 --> 08:26.640
Roger: Your ice cream.

08:26.674 --> 08:27.975
**

08:28.008 --> 08:30.077
I'm so jacked up
to go rocket bootin'!

08:30.110 --> 08:31.645
I don't think
I want to do this...

08:31.679 --> 08:32.913
[ Sighs ]

08:32.946 --> 08:35.683
I knew losing your arm
wouldn't change you.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.785
...because I'd rather
do that.

08:39.452 --> 08:40.588
Aah!

08:40.621 --> 08:42.155
Aww!

08:42.189 --> 08:44.892
Aah!
This is amazing!

08:44.925 --> 08:46.660
I'm lovin'
the new Steve.

08:46.694 --> 08:48.428
Stump-bump it!

08:48.461 --> 08:50.931
Maybe after it heals.

08:50.964 --> 08:52.600
[ Audience booing
on television ]

08:52.633 --> 08:56.236
You know,
after hearing both sides,

08:56.269 --> 08:58.338
I'm kind of with
these deadbeat dads.

08:58.371 --> 09:01.274
Hey, Klaus, you remember
my friend Danuta, right?

09:01.308 --> 09:02.576
Of course.

09:02.610 --> 09:04.878
Bangin' bod.
Super long fingers.

09:04.912 --> 09:06.847
Total smoke show.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.683
Well, the other day,
she said you were "kinda hot."

09:09.717 --> 09:11.084
You wouldn't be interested,
would you?

09:11.118 --> 09:13.921
Yeah, baby!
It's on!

09:13.954 --> 09:15.589
Nothing like
a sure thing.

09:15.623 --> 09:18.525
She's fine as hell,
and I'm...

09:18.558 --> 09:20.861
gonna blow it.

09:20.894 --> 09:23.463
I can't bag
a dime like Danuta.

09:23.496 --> 09:25.966
Agh!
She's too hot!

09:25.999 --> 09:27.267
Agh!

09:27.300 --> 09:28.802
Wait, are you
messing with me?

09:28.836 --> 09:30.303
I will kill you!

09:30.337 --> 09:32.239
Relax!
I'm not messing with you.

09:32.272 --> 09:34.074
Call her. Right now.
Prove it.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.809
I don't really think
that's necessary.

09:35.843 --> 09:37.310
[ Growling ] Do it.

09:37.344 --> 09:39.412
Okay, okay!

09:39.446 --> 09:40.648
[ Cellphone beeps, ringing ]

09:40.681 --> 09:41.749
Danuta:
'Sup, whore?

09:41.782 --> 09:42.916
What up, 'Nutes?

09:42.950 --> 09:44.317
So, um...

09:44.351 --> 09:46.119
who was I supposed
to set you up with again?

09:46.153 --> 09:47.988
Klaus.
He's kinda hot.

09:48.021 --> 09:51.058
[ Moans ]

09:51.091 --> 09:52.592
What's that noise?

09:52.626 --> 09:55.328
Uh, Wendy Williams is benching
300 pounds on her show!

09:55.362 --> 09:56.429
Oh, my God,
she's really doing it!

09:56.463 --> 09:57.597
Bye!
[ Cellphone beeps ]

09:57.631 --> 09:59.232
There you go.
Believe it now?

09:59.266 --> 10:02.335
Ohhh, that broad
was built to bang!

10:02.369 --> 10:04.171
You really shouldn't let her
call you a whore.

10:04.204 --> 10:06.606
I-I know it's a joke,
but it's just kind of bad

10:06.640 --> 10:08.308
for women in general,
you know?

10:08.341 --> 10:11.511
Oh, and tell Danuta
to get fully waxed.

10:11.544 --> 10:14.081
But not the butthole.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.916
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

10:15.949 --> 10:18.185
Damn.
We high up.

10:18.218 --> 10:19.753
Didn't even notice.

10:19.787 --> 10:21.689
You know, I think all my fear
was in that arm.

10:21.722 --> 10:23.456
You guys should really consider
cutting yours off.

10:23.490 --> 10:25.025
Hey, how cool
is the view?

10:25.058 --> 10:27.127
Think that's cool?
Check this out.

10:27.160 --> 10:29.930
Lifted it
from my old man.

10:29.963 --> 10:31.264
So badass!

10:31.298 --> 10:32.700
Okay, Steve,
stop messing around.

10:32.733 --> 10:34.868
We're just having
a good time.
Quit it.

10:34.902 --> 10:36.203
Seriously, man,
that's not funny.
What -- What are you
afraid of?

10:36.236 --> 10:37.838
A little pop gun?
Cut it out, Steve!

10:37.871 --> 10:39.339
Stop playing around, man!
Pop! Pop! Pop!
[ Laughs ]

10:39.372 --> 10:40.974
Hey, Stan,
just checking in.

10:41.008 --> 10:43.310
You still think
Steve's doing great?
Yep.

10:43.343 --> 10:44.644
Really? You don't --
You don't think he's

10:44.678 --> 10:46.646
acting a bit...

10:46.680 --> 10:48.215
reckless?
No.

10:48.248 --> 10:49.983
Just the other day,
he made Toshi give him

10:50.017 --> 10:52.552
a lower-back tattoo
with a rusty paperclip.

10:52.585 --> 10:54.121
It's a Ninja Turtle.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.455
Yeah, Raphael.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.024
He's the rude dude
of the group.

10:57.057 --> 10:58.625
Steve is clearly
out of control.

10:58.658 --> 11:00.794
Well, it's better than
being afraid of the world.

11:00.828 --> 11:03.396
He put his whole mouth
around the water-fountain spout

11:03.430 --> 11:05.132
at the little-league park!
I saw it!

11:05.165 --> 11:06.566
The boy's just getting it
all out of his system.

11:06.599 --> 11:07.634
He'll be fine.

11:07.667 --> 11:11.671
[ Steve laughing maniacally ]

11:11.705 --> 11:13.573
Argh!
[ Laughing muffledly ]

11:13.606 --> 11:14.842
[ Snake hisses ]

11:14.875 --> 11:17.344
Classic horseplay.

11:17.377 --> 11:19.847
**

11:19.880 --> 11:22.582
[ Can hisses ]

11:22.615 --> 11:24.551
[ Door opens, closes ]
[ Sniffs ]

11:24.584 --> 11:26.319
Francine,
have you seen Steve?

11:26.353 --> 11:28.922
Buscemi?
Everywhere.

11:28.956 --> 11:31.892
But that might be
the Lemon Pledge talking.

11:31.925 --> 11:33.226
We're looking
for Steve,

11:33.260 --> 11:34.895
the child
you occasionally mother

11:34.928 --> 11:36.429
in your more lucid
moments.

11:36.463 --> 11:39.066
Oh, he said he was going
to the comic-book store

11:39.099 --> 11:40.600
to do battle or something.

11:40.633 --> 11:43.871
See, Roger? He's back to playing
his Pokémon cards.

11:43.904 --> 11:45.405
Jesus,
Mary, and Joseph!

11:45.438 --> 11:46.706
He left his Bulbasaur!

11:46.740 --> 11:48.241
He might as well
be going to battle

11:48.275 --> 11:49.743
with an army
of Jigglypuffs.

11:49.777 --> 11:51.678
Relax, I'm sure
Steve has a Hoobastank

11:51.711 --> 11:53.713
or a couple of Chumbawambas
up his sleeve.

11:53.747 --> 11:56.183
This is pretty reckless behavior
if you ask me.

11:56.216 --> 11:58.351
Fine. We'll bring him
his stupid card.

11:58.385 --> 12:00.220
Now, where was I?
[ Door opens, closes ]

12:00.253 --> 12:03.757
So, what was it like
working with Tarantino?

12:03.791 --> 12:05.058
[ Imitating Steve Buscemi ]
I don't know.

12:05.092 --> 12:07.060
What's it like
being so beautiful?

12:07.094 --> 12:08.728
[ Giggles ]

12:08.762 --> 12:11.231
**

12:11.264 --> 12:13.967
Yo, neckbeard.
You seen a kid?

12:14.001 --> 12:15.435
We're looking
for Steve Smith.

12:15.468 --> 12:19.406
Oh, thank God
you're here for him.

12:19.439 --> 12:20.874
[ Steve laughing ]

12:20.908 --> 12:22.776
That's been non-stop.

12:22.810 --> 12:24.978
Oh, that?
The boy's a bit of a gigglepuss.

12:25.012 --> 12:28.248
A true chuckle-nut.
Guffaw-hound, really.

12:28.281 --> 12:29.549
Probably just tickle...

12:29.582 --> 12:31.718
fighting?

12:31.751 --> 12:33.453
[ Laughing maniacally ]

12:33.486 --> 12:35.655
I feel so alive!

12:35.688 --> 12:36.924
[ Spits ]

12:36.957 --> 12:38.826
[ Tooth clacks ]

12:38.859 --> 12:40.127
Oh, hey, Dad.

12:40.160 --> 12:41.561
Lose the shirt
and hop in the ring.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.897
Snot's been dying to fight you
for years.

12:43.931 --> 12:46.766
Oh, Snot will get his.
But he will not see it coming.

12:46.800 --> 12:48.101
I'm worried about you,
son.

12:48.135 --> 12:49.970
Why?
I'm on top of the world.

12:50.003 --> 12:52.572
Roger, could you give me
a...hand?

12:52.605 --> 12:55.275
[ Gagging ]

12:55.308 --> 12:56.109
[ Splat ]

12:56.143 --> 12:58.178
[ Gagging ]

12:58.211 --> 12:59.646
[ Splat ]

12:59.679 --> 13:00.948
[ Gulps ]

13:00.981 --> 13:02.950
What the hell is going on
inside you?

13:02.983 --> 13:05.352
Is that...my arm?

13:05.385 --> 13:08.455
Steve, Roger and I staged
the entire attack.

13:08.488 --> 13:09.689
I was the shark!

13:09.722 --> 13:12.993
So...I never confronted
anything?

13:13.026 --> 13:16.529
All my confidence
is based on a lie?

13:16.563 --> 13:19.199
Oh, my God,
is this my blood?!

13:19.232 --> 13:20.968
Aaaah-ha-ha-ha!

13:22.502 --> 13:24.537
We got our Steve back.

13:24.571 --> 13:27.007
I haven't changed
at all.

13:27.040 --> 13:28.108
Chin up, buddy.

13:28.141 --> 13:29.542
[ Laughs ]
There, there.

13:29.576 --> 13:31.444
More! More! More!

13:31.478 --> 13:33.480
Ay, paisan,
you angry?

13:33.513 --> 13:35.148
Then why don't you tell me
to fon-jewel!

13:35.182 --> 13:36.483
[ Both laugh ]

13:36.516 --> 13:37.817
You want in
on this?

13:39.086 --> 13:40.520
Uh -- Oh!

13:40.553 --> 13:41.989
Look what I caught
Steve doin'!

13:42.022 --> 13:43.290
[ Both laugh ]

13:43.323 --> 13:45.458
Come on, Klaus,
just call Danuta.

13:45.492 --> 13:48.295
Um, calling a girl
is so desperate.

13:48.328 --> 13:50.030
Can't I just draw a penis
on a brick

13:50.063 --> 13:52.065
and throw it through her
family's living-room window?

13:52.099 --> 13:53.133
Are you nervous?

13:53.166 --> 13:54.567
No, I'm not nervous.

13:55.668 --> 13:57.237
[ Telephone beeps ]
This phone's nervous.

13:57.270 --> 13:58.571
[ Beeping continues ]

13:58.605 --> 14:02.075
[ Cellphone vibrates, beeps ]
Hello?

14:02.109 --> 14:03.143
[ Deadpan ] Danuta.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.345
Who is this?

14:05.378 --> 14:06.679
Danuta.

14:06.713 --> 14:08.848
Who's calling?

14:08.882 --> 14:10.250
It is me.

14:10.283 --> 14:12.252
What?

14:12.285 --> 14:13.686
Will you go there?

14:13.720 --> 14:16.356
Go where?
What?

14:16.389 --> 14:17.724
Do you eat?

14:17.757 --> 14:19.492
What the hell
is this?!

14:19.526 --> 14:22.862
I've got the money...

14:22.896 --> 14:23.931
Danuta.

14:23.964 --> 14:25.032
[ Bang ]

14:25.065 --> 14:27.000
Klaus,
that was...chilling.

14:27.034 --> 14:28.268
I blacked out.

14:28.301 --> 14:29.836
Hey, let's just
take the pressure off.

14:29.869 --> 14:31.204
M-Make it a group date.

14:31.238 --> 14:33.240
Do you have any friends
you could invite?

14:33.273 --> 14:35.408
[ Scoffing ]
Do I have any friends?

14:35.442 --> 14:38.411
Someone's obviously forgotten
about my boy Jurgen.

14:38.445 --> 14:39.879
How could I forget
about a guy

14:39.913 --> 14:42.715
I caught stealing used Q-tips
out of my trash can?

14:42.749 --> 14:45.852
Exactly!
He's unforgettable.

14:45.885 --> 14:48.355
**

14:48.388 --> 14:49.589
Knock, knock.

14:49.622 --> 14:52.092
Any two-armed boys
in here?

14:52.125 --> 14:54.061
Would you settle
for a two-armed man

14:54.094 --> 14:55.295
who was hospitalized
for eating

14:55.328 --> 14:57.664
an entire
American Girl doll?

14:59.566 --> 15:00.867
Where'd my son go?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.769
He said something about
living a lie

15:02.802 --> 15:06.373
and needing to conquer his fear
by killing a shark.

15:06.406 --> 15:08.808
**

15:08.841 --> 15:10.877
Your bloodthirsty quest
reminds me

15:10.910 --> 15:13.546
of my childhood
in Bon Temps, Louisiana.

15:13.580 --> 15:17.050
Yes, I am from the town
in "True Blood,"

15:17.084 --> 15:18.718
but at the time,
I was unawares

15:18.751 --> 15:22.222
of any goings on
of any vampire shenanigans.

15:22.255 --> 15:26.126
Oh, that town was overrun
with vampires!

15:26.159 --> 15:27.660
And many of the dogs
I would see

15:27.694 --> 15:30.430
I would later realize
were werewolves.

15:33.300 --> 15:35.102
**

15:35.135 --> 15:37.237
Hurry, Roger!
We gotta stop Steve

15:37.270 --> 15:38.838
before he throws down
with a shark.

15:38.871 --> 15:42.275
Easy, Stan. I'm takin' ya
straight to great-white country.

15:42.309 --> 15:44.344
Just need to make
a little detour.

15:44.377 --> 15:46.446
There's a sunken wheelchair
around here.

15:46.479 --> 15:48.415
My theory?
I think it fell off a boat.

15:48.448 --> 15:51.484
Roger, my son's gonna die,
and it's all my fault.

15:51.518 --> 15:54.954
Unless...some guy wheeled it
across the ocean floor?

15:54.988 --> 15:56.923
Is that your theory,
Stan?

15:56.956 --> 15:58.325
Yes, yes,
talk me through it.

15:58.358 --> 15:59.792
I think
I could be convinced.

15:59.826 --> 16:03.863
**

16:03.896 --> 16:05.132
Say something to her.

16:05.165 --> 16:08.335
[ Clears throat ]
Danuta, um...

16:08.368 --> 16:10.870
what's, like, the grossest
disease you've ever gotten?

16:10.903 --> 16:14.207
Um...I don't know.
Gingivitis?

16:14.241 --> 16:15.975
[ Chuckles ] Oh-ho-ho.
That's it?

16:16.009 --> 16:17.644
Play your cards right,

16:17.677 --> 16:20.180
and later I'll give you
something much worse.

16:20.213 --> 16:21.881
You're funny.

16:21.914 --> 16:23.450
Jurgen, put me down.

16:23.483 --> 16:26.719
Let me win shorty over here
a stuffed Munion.

16:26.753 --> 16:30.190
**

16:30.223 --> 16:34.494
Someone call a doctor,
'cause my jump shot is sick!

16:34.527 --> 16:35.695
[ Basketball bounces ]

16:35.728 --> 16:37.230
[ Chuckles
awkwardly ]

16:37.264 --> 16:39.866
Just clearing out
the cobwebs.

16:39.899 --> 16:40.900
Tell 'em, Jurgen.

16:40.933 --> 16:41.968
Yep.

16:42.001 --> 16:44.537
**

16:44.571 --> 16:45.838
Swish!

16:45.872 --> 16:47.640
[ Smack ]
[ Cries ]

16:47.674 --> 16:50.243
Klaus,
maybe we should move on.

16:50.277 --> 16:52.412
I'm winning her
a prize!

16:52.445 --> 16:53.380
[ Smack ]

16:53.413 --> 16:54.481
[ Smack ]

16:54.514 --> 16:56.549
[ Smack ]
[ Gags ]

16:56.583 --> 16:58.918
Why don't
we go on a ride?

16:58.951 --> 17:00.753
Besides,
there's someone

17:00.787 --> 17:02.922
I'd rather cuddle with
than a stuffed animal.

17:02.955 --> 17:05.392
How can I concentrate
with you jabbering in my ear?!

17:05.425 --> 17:08.695
You keep begging me and begging
me for this [bleep] Munion,

17:08.728 --> 17:10.863
then flap your lips
every time I take a shot!

17:10.897 --> 17:12.765
I'm...sorry?

17:12.799 --> 17:14.201
Take a lap, Danuta.

17:14.234 --> 17:17.104
All of you!
Just let me work.

17:17.137 --> 17:18.938
[ Smack ]
[ Cat yowls ]

17:18.971 --> 17:21.441
**

17:21.474 --> 17:23.276
Where are
these damn sharks?

17:23.310 --> 17:24.577
While we're waitin',
can I interest you

17:24.611 --> 17:26.913
in corn hole,
some beer pong?

17:26.946 --> 17:28.248
[ Clatter ]

17:28.281 --> 17:30.683
No! I'm -- I'm trying
to stare down death.

17:30.717 --> 17:31.918
Why do you have
all this stuff?

17:31.951 --> 17:33.853
'Cause this here's
a party boat.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.588
I wish
I could pay the bills

17:35.622 --> 17:37.124
taking one-armed boys
shark-killing

17:37.157 --> 17:38.858
to prove
how brave they are,

17:38.891 --> 17:41.528
but, sadly, that's just not
the world we're living in.

17:41.561 --> 17:44.864
Now, are we going to buttchug
some Southern Comfort or --

17:44.897 --> 17:47.267
Shark!

17:47.300 --> 17:50.603
This is it.
Time to conquer my fears.

17:50.637 --> 17:52.105
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

17:52.139 --> 17:54.307
Yaaah!

17:55.608 --> 17:57.910
Yes! I did it!

17:57.944 --> 17:58.978
Oh.

17:59.011 --> 18:00.247
Well,
butter my biscuit.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.215
You killed
a cute, little baby.

18:02.249 --> 18:04.951
Wahh! Wahh!
Change my diaper!

18:04.984 --> 18:06.486
Don't murder me!

18:06.519 --> 18:09.289
And I'm guessin'
that's his ma and pa.

18:09.322 --> 18:11.791
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

18:11.824 --> 18:13.793
[ Whimpers ]
Did you know
that sharks can have

18:13.826 --> 18:15.328
up to 50 rows
of teeth?

18:15.362 --> 18:17.330
I'm great
with trivia like that.

18:17.364 --> 18:19.499
Ask me Lady Gaga's
real name.

18:19.532 --> 18:21.100
**

18:21.134 --> 18:23.570
Stefani Germanotta.

18:23.603 --> 18:26.439
$260, $280, $300.

18:26.473 --> 18:28.175
Now give me
the damn prize!

18:30.143 --> 18:33.946
Finally, the Munion-shaped key
to Danuta's heart.

18:33.980 --> 18:35.515
Now, where is she?

18:35.548 --> 18:37.684
[ Moaning ]

18:37.717 --> 18:39.486
Jurgen...
Yep.

18:39.519 --> 18:42.655
[ Moaning ]

18:42.689 --> 18:47.026
Danuta!

18:47.059 --> 18:48.461
I'm sorry, Klaus.

18:48.495 --> 18:50.129
It's my fault.

18:50.163 --> 18:52.932
For bringing that wolf Jurgen
into the hen house.

18:52.965 --> 18:54.534
Players
are gonna play,

18:54.567 --> 18:57.003
and I, of all people,
should know that.

18:57.036 --> 18:58.271
Don't worry.

18:58.305 --> 18:59.772
There's somebody out there
for everyone.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.841
You'll find yours
some day.

19:03.376 --> 19:04.711
What are you doing?!

19:04.744 --> 19:06.779
I-I thought you were
putting out the vibe.

19:06.813 --> 19:08.181
Are you kidding me?

19:08.215 --> 19:09.216
No!

19:09.249 --> 19:11.551
[ Splash ]

19:11.584 --> 19:13.052
[ Laughter, playful screaming
in distance ]

19:13.085 --> 19:14.487
I give up.

19:16.022 --> 19:17.056
[ Whir, explosion ]

19:17.089 --> 19:19.826
[ Screaming ]

19:19.859 --> 19:22.028
Whoa!
That was crazy!

19:22.061 --> 19:24.130
Why isn't anyone
reacting to this?

19:24.163 --> 19:26.533
Because it doesn't
concern me.

19:26.566 --> 19:28.735
I'm not
in the Gravitron.

19:28.768 --> 19:32.672
I'm eating caramel corn,
having the time of my life.

19:32.705 --> 19:35.141
This is a carnival,
after all.

19:35.174 --> 19:37.344
Try smiling, asshole!

19:37.377 --> 19:41.248
[Bleep] you!

19:41.281 --> 19:44.517
**

19:44.551 --> 19:45.418
Aah!

19:45.452 --> 19:46.386
[ Splash ]
Ferryman!

19:46.419 --> 19:47.520
You save Steve.

19:47.554 --> 19:50.723
I'll lead
the sharks away.

19:50.757 --> 19:53.260
[ Dramatic music plays ]

19:53.293 --> 19:54.561
Betcha can't catch --

19:54.594 --> 19:55.895
Aah!

19:55.928 --> 19:57.697
Steve, we have
to get out of here.

19:57.730 --> 20:00.833
No. I have to face those sharks
and prove I'm not afraid.

20:00.867 --> 20:01.868
No, you don't.

20:01.901 --> 20:03.270
It's okay to be afraid.

20:03.303 --> 20:05.004
Fear is what keeps us alive.

20:05.037 --> 20:07.173
But you're not afraid
of anything.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.375
Yes, I am.

20:08.408 --> 20:10.377
I'm afraid
of losing you.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.744
That and people
finding out

20:11.778 --> 20:14.514
I can't pronounce the word
"dorktor's oyfoice."

20:14.547 --> 20:17.216
Are you trying to say
"doctor's office"?

20:17.250 --> 20:18.585
God, it's so easy
for you!

20:18.618 --> 20:19.886
Roger: Little help?

20:19.919 --> 20:22.121
Anyone got
an Oral-B floss pick?

20:22.154 --> 20:23.423
[ Laughs ]
Ow!

20:23.456 --> 20:25.091
We have to save Roger!

20:25.124 --> 20:27.193
No, Steve,
listen to your fears.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.228
We have
to save ourselves first.

20:29.262 --> 20:30.963
When Roger
washes up on shore,

20:30.997 --> 20:32.732
we can take him
to the emerghmancy rom.

20:32.765 --> 20:35.067
Okay.
But how do we get out of...

20:35.101 --> 20:37.704
Wait!
This is a party boat.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.572
Maybe they have --
[ Gasps ]

20:39.606 --> 20:43.376
**

20:43.410 --> 20:44.411
[ Ting! ]

20:44.444 --> 20:46.245
Dang.

20:48.648 --> 20:50.049
* We get lifted

20:50.082 --> 20:52.285
Look at us, Dad!

20:52.319 --> 20:54.554
We're finally doing it!

20:54.587 --> 20:55.788
I'm the one
friggin' doing it.

20:55.822 --> 20:56.989
* We get lifted

20:57.023 --> 20:58.658
* Oh
* We get light

20:58.691 --> 21:02.128
Why y'all heading
further out to sea?

21:02.161 --> 21:03.963
Bye! Have a great time!
